proposals/composition_engine.md:149:**Problem.** Basis topology alone is not enough for a latent coordinate. A cyclic basis can make `Φ(t)` continuous across the seam, but if the per-row coordinate update is Euclidean then an angular latent still has a spurious discontinuity at `2π → 0`. mGPLVM avoids this by putting the latent itself on the manifold (circle, sphere, torus, product manifolds) and optimizing with Riemannian updates.
